    abstract = {In Continual Learning settings, deep neural networks are prone to Catastrophic Forgetting. Orthogonal Gradient Descent was proposed to tackle the challenge. However, no theoretical guarantees have been proven yet. We present a theoretical framework to study Continual Learning algorithms in the Neural Tangent Kernel regime. This framework comprises closed form expression of the model through tasks and proxies for Transfer Learning, generalisation and tasks similarity. In this framework, we prove that {OGD} is robust to Catastrophic Forgetting then derive the ﬁrst generalisation bound for {SGD} and {OGD} for Continual Learning. Finally, we study the limits of this framework in practice for {OGD} and highlight the importance of the Neural Tangent Kernel variation for Continual Learning with {OGD}.},
